2.caption: 1970 East–West Pro Bowl
2.description: The 1970 Pro Bowl was the National Football League's twentieth annual all-star game which featured the outstanding performers from the 1969 season. The game was played on Sunday, January 18, 1970, at Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum in Los Angeles. The final score was West 16, East 13. Gale Sayers of the Chicago Bears was named the game's offensive Most Valuable Player (MVP) after rushing for 75 yards on nine carries. George Andrie of the Dallas Cowboys was selected as the defensive MVP.
2.inspected:Announcers: Don Criqui, Frank Gifford, Frank Glieber
2.inspected:Co-MVPs: Gale Sayers (Chicago Bears), George Andrie (Dallas Cowboys)
